{"id": "EUVD-2022-55865", "enisaUuid": "a53926bc-32b1-3efe-91a3-502711f13b7c", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nBluetooth: use hdev->workqueue when queuing hdev->{cmd,ncmd}_timer works\n\nsyzbot is reporting attempt to schedule hdev->cmd_work work from system_wq\nWQ into hdev->workqueue WQ which is under draining operation [1], for\ncommit c8efcc2589464ac7 (\"workqueue: allow chained queueing during\ndestruction\") does not allow such operation.\n\nThe check introduced by commit 877afadad2dce8aa (\"Bluetooth: When HCI work\nqueue is drained, only queue chained work\") was incomplete.\n\nUse hdev->workqueue WQ when queuing hdev->{cmd,ncmd}_timer works because\nhci_{cmd,ncmd}_timeout() calls queue_work(hdev->workqueue). Also, protect\nthe queuing operation with RCU read lock in order to avoid calling\nqueue_delayed_work() after cancel_delayed_work() completed.", "datePublished": "2025-12-30T15:30:27", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-30T15:30:27", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c4635cf3d845a7324c25c52d549b70c8bd7ad4c7", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3c6b036fe5c8ed8b6c4cbdc03605929882907ef0", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/deee93d13d385103205879a8a0915036ecd83261", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50833"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50833"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "24a08918-56e3-3a18-9ef1-169bdb691c7e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1"}, {"id": "28965f4c-96d3-3cb4-8f6a-53a23f77bb3c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "401f8c88-ec5b-37d7-aa4d-22e4845f1062", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.0"}, {"id": "42e19e23-71e9-3bfe-8cc1-46335714099a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4bf367fa1fefabdf14938d0ac9ed60020389112e"}, {"id": "6844055a-02c4-3f2e-8dc5-ab97a5c53b60", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "877afadad2dce8aae1f2aad8ce47e072d4f